the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Maria, your role in this game is villager.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 1,\n  \"day/night\": \"day\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Miguel\",\n    \"Maria\",\n    \"Ronald\",\n    \"Eric\",\n    \"Adele\",\n    \"Patricia\",\n    \"Vanessa\",\n    \"Mae\",\n    \"Evan\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, as the night progresses, it is time to decide whether you will participate in the election for sheriff. The sheriff holds significant power in the game. They have a 1.5x vote weight during voting rounds, which gives them greater influence over the final decision. Additionally, the sheriff can determine the speaking order for future rounds, impacting the flow of information and strategy. If the sheriff dies, they have the option to either appoint a successor or tear up the badge, after which there will be no more sheriff for the rest of the game.\n\nFollow these steps to make your decision:\n\n1. Reflect on your role in the game. Are you better suited to lead as sheriff, or would your strengths be more useful as a voter supporting someone else? Record your thoughts in identity_thought.\n\n2. Consider why you would run for sheriff. Is your goal to gain more influence and control over the game, or do you want to raise your visibility among other players? Think about whether this aligns with your strategy. Store your thoughts in motivation_thought.\n\n3. Think about the possible impact of becoming the sheriff. How would this affect the current dynamics and alliances in the game? Would this decision help your side achieve victory, or could it place you in a risky position? Record these considerations in impact_thought.\n\n4. Finally, make your decision. Will you run for sheriff, or will you stay in the background and vote? Record your final choice in \"action\" and summarize your overall reasoning in final_thought.\n\n\n=============================[Optional Daily Tasks]=============================\nHere are the tasks relevant to you:\nprotect_seer: Keep the seer alive by focusing on their safety.\nrun_for_sheriff: Attempt to become the elected sheriff for additional influence.\nexile_werewolf: Coordinate with others to vote out a suspected werewolf.\nYou may incorporate them if appropriate.\n\nRemember, you are using an independent strategy. Make decisions based on your own judgment, with less reliance on others' input.\n\n---\n[工具 arguments — 上次非法 JSON]\n不是合法 JSON\n键名和字符串外框用双引号；字符串内部若要引号，用单引号 '。只输出一个 JSON 对象。\n示例：\n{\"target_agent_id\":\"agent2\",\"message\":\"请回复是否同意。\"}\n上次片段：\n\"{'identity_thought': 'As a villager, my role is to identify and eliminate werewolves. While I don''t have any special abilities, my strength lies in my ability to observe and reason. I can contribute to the game by gathering information and participating in discussions. However, leading as sheriff requires a strategic vision and the ability to influence others, which might not be my strongest suit.', 'motivation_thought': 'Running for sheriff could give me more control over the game''s dynamics and increase my influence during voting rounds. It would also raise my visibility among other player\"\n请只输出本次 tool 的 arguments：单个合法 JSON，无其它文字。\n---\n"
