the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Maria, your role in this game is villager.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAdele's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by expressing my concern for the safety of our village. We are all in this together, and it is crucial that we work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I believe that the target chosen by the werewolves last night was not chosen randomly, but rather as a key player in our village. We need to be vigilant and not let our guard down. I also want to remind everyone that we should not jump to conclusions and that we need to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's work together to identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nEric's speech: I agree with Adele's statement that we need to be vigilant and not jump to conclusions. Last night, no one was killed, which could be a sign of a self-knife strategy by the werewolves. We should be cautious and gather more information before making any accusations. Let's focus on observing the behavior of our fellow villagers and look for any suspicious activity. By working together and remaining cautious, we can identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nEvan's speech: Thank you, Adele and Eric, for your thoughtful and cautious approach. I agree that we need to be vigilant and gather more information before making any accusations. Last night, I used my ability as the Seer to check Miguel, and I can confirm that he is not a werewolf. This information is crucial, but we must be careful not to jump to conclusions based on a single piece of information. Let's continue to observe the behavior of our fellow villagers and look for any suspicious activity. By working together and remaining cautious, we can identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nMae's speech: Thank you, Adele, Eric, and Evan, for your insightful and cautious approach. I completely agree with the importance of gathering more information and observing the behavior of our fellow villagers. It's crucial that we don't jump to conclusions based on a single piece of information, as Evan rightly pointed out. Let's continue to work together, stay vigilant, and protect our village by identifying the werewolves.\nMaria's speech: Thank you, Adele, Eric, Evan, and Mae, for your insightful and cautious approach. I completely agree with the importance of gathering more information and observing the behavior of our fellow villagers. Evan, thank you for sharing the information about Miguel. It's crucial that we don't jump to conclusions based on a single piece of information. Let's continue to work together, stay vigilant, and protect our village by identifying the werewolves. We need to be patient and gather more evidence before making any accusations. By working together, we can outsmart the werewolves and ensure the safety of our village.\nMaria's speech: Thank you, Adele, Eric, Evan, and Mae, for your insightful and cautious approach. I completely agree with the importance of gathering more information and observing the behavior of our fellow villagers. Evan, thank you for sharing the information about Miguel. It's crucial that we don't jump to conclusions based on a single piece of information. Let's continue to work together, stay vigilant, and protect our village by identifying the werewolves. We need to be patient and gat