er and the Witch working together is essential for our village's survival. Let's continue to observe our fellow villagers and work together to identify the werewolves.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\nNo player was banished due to a tie.\nBanishment votes:\nMiguel voted for abstain\nMaria voted for abstain\nRonald voted for Miguel\nEric voted for abstain\nAdele voted for Patricia\nPatricia voted for Eric\nVanessa voted for Maria\nMae voted for Maria\nEvan voted for Miguel\n(Note: The voting order reflects only the system's query sequence and does not imply any strategic alignment or motive.)\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 2\nSYSTEM: Night 2 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 2 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Ronald\nPlayer Ronald has been eliminated from the game.\nAdele's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by thanking Evan for sharing the confirmation about Miguel. This information is crucial and supports the idea that the werewolves might be using a self-knife strategy to mislead us. We need to remain vigilant and gather more information before making any accusations. I also want to express my support for the Guard's role in protecting key players like the Seer. By working together and staying cautious, we can identify the werewolves and protect our village. We are all in this together, and only by working together can we ensure the safety of our village.\nEric's speech: Thank you, Adele, for your supportive speech and for emphasizing the importance of the Guard's role in protecting key players like the Seer. I completely agree with your cautious approach. It's crucial that we remain vigilant and gather more information before making any accusations. We should all be observi