e werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Mae, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Adele': 'Ronald', 'Patricia': 'Eric', 'Mae': 'Eric'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Adele', 'Patricia', 'Mae']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: Eric\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nAdele's speech: Good morning, everyone. I want to start by expressing my concern for the safety of our village. We are all in this together, and it is crucial that we work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I believe that the target chosen by the werewolves last night was not chosen randomly, but rather as a key player in our village. We need to be vigilant and not let our guard down. I also want to remind everyone that we should not jump to conclusions and that we need to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's work together to identify the werewolves and protect our village.\nEric's speech: I agree with Adele's statement that we need to be vigilant and not jump to conclusions. Last night, no one was killed, which could be a sign of a self-knife strategy by the werewolves. We should be cautious and gather more information before making any accusations. Let's focus on observing the behavior of our fellow villagers and look for any suspicious activity. By working together and remaining cautious, we can identify the werewolves and